  "learn": {
    "heading": "Multiply across a sum",
    "intro": "<p>The <strong>distributive property</strong> says a number times a sum equals that number times each part, added up. Think of an array: 3 rows of (4 + 2) is 3 rows of 4 <em>plus</em> 3 rows of 2.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>3 × (4 + 2)</strong>: add first → 3 × 6 = <strong>18</strong>. Spread out → (3 × 4) + (3 × 2) = 12 + 6 = <strong>18</strong>. Same answer!",
      "<strong>2 × (5 + 1)</strong> = 2 × 6 = 12, and (2 × 5) + (2 × 1) = 10 + 2 = <strong>12</strong>."
    ]
  },
